the whiteled government has 
released the names of 801 people held without charge for at least 
30 days under stateofemergency regulations the great majority 
are black 
the list released tuesday includes many prominent 
antiapartheid activists who have been held for most or all of the 
state of emergency declared on june 12 1986 
among them are zwalakhe sisulu editor of the blackoriented 
newspaper new nation and murphy morobe chief spokesman for the 
nowbanned united democratic front coalition 
virtually all the detainees on the list are black but among 
them are a handful of whites the only white held for the entire 
emergency is raymond suttner a law lecturer at the university of 
the witwatersrand 
the government is not required to report the names of detainess 
held less than 30 days and has never issued comprehensive figures 
for the number of detentions during the emergency 
monitoring groups estimate that 30000 people have been held for 
varying periods 
