<TEXT>
here is a chronology of the main 
political events in chile since gen augusto pinochet seized power 
in a coup 15 years ago 
sept 11 1973 pinochet leads the armed forces in a bloody 
coup that overthrows president salvador allende a marxist elected 
in 1970 allende dies in the coup and the new government says he 
committed suicide his supporters say he was killed a fourmen 
military junta led by pinochet takes power and represses supporters 
of the ousted leftist government hundreds of leftists are killed 
or disappear after being arrested thousands are sent to 
concentration camps or into exile congress is closed and political 
activity prohibited 
june 20 1974 pinochet becomes supreme chief of the nation 
retaining his post as president of the military junta 
oct 29 1974 exiled former army commander gen carlos prats 
and his wife are killed by a bomb in buenos aires argentina and 
involvement by chilean secret police is suspected the same charge 
arises when an exiled former foreign minister orlando letelier is 
killed in a sept 21 1976 bombing in washington a us court 
indicts three highranking chilean army officers in the case but 
chile refuses to extradite them 
july 9 1977 pinochet outlines a farreaching political and 
institutional program calling for the military to remain in power 
at least 11 more years 
jan 4 1978 pinochet faced with growing international and 
domestic comdemnation of human rights abuse calls a national 
referendum to seek support from the chilean people he wins the 
ballot but opposition leaders charge widespread fraud 
june 20 1978 air force commander gen gustavo leigh a 
member of the military junta publicly challenges pinochets 
authority by disagreeing with the government political program 
pinochet ousts leigh from the junta and forces him into retirement 
sept 11 1980 pinochet wins approval in a referendum for a 
new constitution that confirms his presidency until march 11 1989 
it also allows him to seek a new period of rule until 1997 the 
opposition again charges massive fraud in the ballot 
march 11 1981 the new constitution goes into effect 
may 11 1983 amid a deep economic crisis the opposition 
stages the first of a series of mass protests against the 
government that left hundreds of dead and thousands arrested 
sept 6 1986 pinochet survives an assassination attempt by a 
leftist urban guerrilla commando five of his bodyguards were 
killed and 11 wounded when the presidential motorcade is ambushed 
on a mountain road outside santiago 
aug 30 1988 the military junta nominates pinochet as the 
sole candidate in an oct 5 presidential referendum sparking 
widespread protests 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

