the simulated failure of space 
shuttle discoverys right engine forced astronauts to shift their 
craft into a low orbit as part of a final rehearsal for the first 
postchallenger mission 
the 56hour simulation began tuesday and involved about 300 
people at johnson space center 
the first thing after launch when they were going into orbit 
the right engine failed so that they had to do whats called abort 
to orbit nasa spokeswoman barbara selby said 
that means the shuttle can still make it into orbit but lower 
than planned so they have to adjust their activities ms selby 
said they did achieve the ato as we call it and made the 
necessary adjustments to continue the mission 
