<TEXT>
the boeing 727 involved in a delta airlines 
crash wednesday at dallasfort worth airport was initially 
designed for short to medium routes and was one of the most popular 
commercial jetliners ever made 
the threeengine plane with the distinctive ttail no longer 
manufactured made its first flight feb 9 1963 it was designed 
for a maximum passenger capacity of about 130 though later models 
could carry 189 passengers 
the plane has a range of more than 2500 statute miles 
production ended aug 14 1984 with 1831 delivered it is flown 
by more than 170 carriers 
there are various models all powered by pratt amp whitney jt8d 
turbofans 
models include 
727100 standard passenger seating 94 length 1332 wingspan 
108 in service feb 1 1964 
727100c same size convertible to all cargo in service april 
23 1966 
727100qc same thing designed for quick conversions to 
passenger or cargo 
727200 length 1532 wingspan 108 134 passengers in 
service dec 14 1967 
727200 advanced version same size 145 passengers in service 
july 1972 
727200f all freight version same size in service august 1983 
