reach a final stage solution between israel and the 
palestinians without jordan 
hussein knows that some day he will be called back to 
negotiate on the final status because without jordan you cant 
solve the problem he knows it very well tamir said 
a month ago hussein announced he was dismantling the legal 
and administrative links between jordan and the west bank a move 
that was seen by some as a setback for hopes that a regional peace 
settlement might be reached 
tamir suggested that it is unrealistic to assume that jordan 
could sever its historical ties to an area it once ruled noting 
that the camp david agreement envisions a role for jordan in the 
final stages of negotiations 
at the same time there have been repeated hints over the past 
month that husseins move may induce the palestine liberation 
organization to initiate a proposal for peace with israel 
tamir who is here for talks with us officials said there is 
an urgent need to end the turmoil in the occupied territories and 
move toward a settlement through negotiations 
as a result of palestinian unrest dating back eight months a 
very dangerous situation has been created he said adding that 
it would be unwise to allow the status quo to exist much longer 
he rejected the view of those who say that israel can wait and 
wait and wait expecting that the arabs will crawl on their 
knees and be ready to accept a peace on the basis of our 
conditions 
to get a negotiating process started tamir said we have to 
mobilize all forces starting with the united states and egypt in 
support an effort to reach an interim agreement with leaders of the 
west bank and the gaza strip 
as long a serious peace talks are delayed he said the uprising 
in the territories will continue and that the situation could 
deteriorate into another arabisraeli war 
