rate 
in the course of those accidents another problem was revealed 
reich said in the early models lines brought fuel along the top 
of the fuselage from the wings to the three engines at the rear 
which meant that in accidents coach passengers would be doused 
with burning fuel within a few years the lines were repositioned 
to the bottom portion of the fuselage 
