<TEXT>
entertainer merv griffin has received 
approval from a majority of resorts international inc stockholders 
to buy the gaming and real estate company but state gaming 
regulators have thrown up a roadblock 
griffins proposed trust agreement needed before he can buy 
the resorts stock from class a shareholders and controlling 
stockholder donald trump failed to win approval tuesday from the 
state casino control commission 
the trust agreement is necessary in case the commission finds 
griffin ineligible for a new jersey gaming license in that case 
the trust would run the company until griffin could appeal the 
decision or sell off the companys assets 
the commission voted 32 against the proposed trust agreement 
largely because it calls for a trustee to take control of the 
griffin co rather than just the resorts stock griffin officials 
wanted the trust agreement to cover the griffin co to ensure the 
firm can take advantage of prior tax losses of resorts potentially 
worth 100 million 
griffins deal to buy resorts was to expire at midnight tuesday 
but robert trump vice president of the trump organization said 
after the commission meeting that he expected griffin to extend the 
offer for another 30 days 
griffin was present at tuesdays hearing but did not testify 
the former talk show host said afterward he had asked the internal 
revenue service for clarification on the tax issue and he still 
expects the deal to go through 
commissioners carl zeitz and w david waters argued that the 
griffin co did not do enough to satisfy the law concerning the 
structure of the trust 
griffin also must obtain approvals from the atlantic city 
housing authority and the bahamian government where a resorts 
facility is located said resorts president ig jack davis 
the deal also is contingent upon settlement of shareholder 
litigation now pending in the delaware chancery court and another 
lawsuit by showboat hotel casino 
trump who owns resorts class b stock which has 100 times the 
voting power of the class a stock will receive 135 a share or 
about 96 million trump will also receive another 63 million to 
break his management agreement with resorts and he will then buy 
