<TEXT>
bellsouth corp on wednesday unveiled an 
electronic gateway that will allow computer users to reach several 
information services with a single local phone call 
bellsouth the first bell company to offer such a service said 
its transtext universal gateway is available in the atlanta calling 
area after the initial introduction there bellsouth plans to make 
the gateway available in other cities in its ninestate region 
we believe information services are an important segment of 
the telecommunications industry and its important for our 
business to be involved said john r gunter bellsouth vice 
president for information services 
but gunter alluding to several failed attempts by companies to 
launch videotex services said bellsouth will proceed slowly and 
were going to be listening a lot to see how information 
service providers and users respond to the gateway 
us district judge harold greene in modifying the consent 
decree that stripped american telephone amp telegraph co of its 
local bell operating companies ruled last year that bell companies 
could establish gateways to transmit electronic information 
supplied by others he continued to bar them however from 
originating any of the information themselves 
without a gateway computer users with a modem must 
presubscribe to the various information services that are 
available and dial into each one separately they also are billed 
by each separately 
using the bellsouth gateway a computer user needs only to 
subscribe to it and can then dial one phone number to reach 
multiple information services subscribers will be billed by 
bellsouth advanced networks an unregulated subsidiary for use of 
the gateway and for the information services they used 
currently eight services are available through the gateway and 
10 more are scheduled to be added soon the company said 
the services that are already on line offer information about an 
atlanta theater company local and national news the stock market 
and travel among other things one service sponsored by an atlanta 
hospital provides health and fitness information and plans soon to 
offer an online heart test another service allows callers to 
chat electronically with one another 
gunter said the company hoped to sign up 300 customers during 
the initial offering and slowly grow to 1000 in atlanta before 
offering the service in other areas 
gateway charges are 150 per hour from 7 pm to 7 am and 3 
per hour during the other 12 hours of the day users would be 
charged an additional fee depending on how much information they 
access typically about 60 cents during the day and 40 cents at 
night gunter said 
customers also must pay for the cost of access to any of the 
information services on the gateway a couple of the services 
charge nothing but the cost of others range up to 50 an hour 
computer users may pay more for some services obtained through 
the gateway than if they dialed into the service directly but 
depending on the time of day some services may be cheaper through 
the gateway 
for example travel plus which is part of general videotex 
corps delphi service charges 780 an hour on the gateway day 
or night but when a caller dials into delphi and calls up travel 
plus it costs 740 per hour during the evening but 1740 during 
the day the daytime rate reflects the higher cost of data lines 
needed for computer transmissions said jon gilbert marketing 
director of general videotex 
</TEXT>
