<TEXT>
honeywell inc said wednesday it plans to 
sell four units in its space and aviation systems business which 
serve military markets 
the units are its electrooptics division in lexington mass 
training and control systems division in west covina calif 
defense communications and production division in tampa fla and 
signal analysis center in annapolis md honeywell said in a 
prepared statement 
our decision to sell these operations reflects honeywells 
resolve to continue focusing on core businesses where we have a 
competitive advantage to assure that we can achieve our goals 
said james j renier honeywell president and chief executive 
officer 
the units we intend to sell are good businesses which happen 
to fall outside the companys strategic focus renier said 
in the space and aviation business honeywell is focusing on 
three strategic core businesses in the commercial aviation 
military avionics and space markets renier said 
this decision will allow us to concentrate on areas where we 
have significant market shares and will reduce our exposure in 
military markets where our competitive advantage isnt as strong 
he said 
in addition renier indicated proceeds from the sale of the four 
units could be applied to the reduction of debt investment in the 
companys controls businesses or the repurchase of stock 
honeywell said approximately 3500 employees are employed at the 
four units being sold 
the divisions combined sales were about 430 million in 1987 
or about 6 percent of the companys total sales of 67 billion 
honeywells space and aviation business sales totaled 19 billion 
in 1987 
